<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-10-27T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-10-27T18:00:00-05:00" n="379" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d379">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.252/6: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Collier</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-10-27T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">October 27,
                                        1927—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>56. Embassy’s telegram number 161, October 24, 4 p.m. Please cable
                            Department whether you think any material prejudice to negotiations
                            would result if we deferred submittal of draft treaty until the middle
                            of November or thereabouts, so as to allow time for further
                            consideration of question whether to include in draft treaty substance
                            of United States Senate reservation regarding national treatment of
                            shipping.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>